      "id": 1,
      "options": {
        "content": "# MQ Appliance HA/DR Queue Manager Health\n\nThis dashboard is built to rank queue managers **worst health first** by **quad / HA / DR grouping**.\n\n## Assumptions\n- Your Prometheus data includes labels: `qmgr`, `quad`, `ha_pair`, and `dr_pair`\n- You expose or record a metric named `mq_qmgr_health_score`\n- Higher score = worse health\n- Recommended supporting metrics:\n  - `mq_qmgr_status`\n  - `mq_ha_partitioned`\n  - `mq_ha_sync_state`\n  - `mq_dr_status`\n  - `ibmmq_queue_current_depth`\n  - `ibmmq_queue_max_depth`\n\n## Notes\nThe original `mq_appliance_dashboard.json` in the referenced repo is an **appliance hardware/firmware dashboard** and does **not** contain direct queue-manager HA/DR health panels or direct `qmgr`/`channel`/`queue` health tables. This dashboard fills that gap.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "pluginVersion": "11.1.0",
      "title": "Overview",
      "type": "text"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${datasource}"
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "thresholds"
          },
          "mappings": [],
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "green",
                "value": null
              },
              {
                "color": "orange",
                "value": 1
              },
              {
                "color": "red",
                "value": 2
              }
            ]
          },
          "unit": "none"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 4,
        "w": 6,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 4
      },
      "id": 2,
